cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.PL 

The paper deals with learning probabilistic models for planning, which is a core problem in artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves learning from data, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. The use of a hierarchical Bayesian approach and optimization algorithm suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with relational probabilistic planning, which is a subfield of automated planning and scheduling, suggesting that it could belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages and Compilers).
